ClaimDevicesByClaimCode.documentation: Adds device(s) to your account (i.e., claim one or more devices) if and only if you received a claim code with the device(s).

DescribeDevice.documentation: Given a device ID, returns a DescribeDeviceResponse object describing the details of the device.

FinalizeDeviceClaim.documentation:
Given a device ID, finalizes the claim request for the associated device.

Claiming a device consists of initiating a claim, then publishing a device event, and finalizing the claim. For a device of type button, a device event can be published by simply clicking the device.

GetDeviceMethods.documentation: Given a device ID, returns the invokable methods associated with the device.

InitiateDeviceClaim.documentation:
Given a device ID, initiates a claim request for the associated device.

Claiming a device consists of initiating a claim, then publishing a device event, and finalizing the claim. For a device of type button, a device event can be published by simply clicking the device.

InvokeDeviceMethod.documentation: Given a device ID, issues a request to invoke a named device method (with possible parameters). See the "Example POST" code snippet below.

ListDeviceEvents.documentation: Using a device ID, returns a DeviceEventsResponse object containing an array of events for the device.

ListDevices.documentation: Lists the 1-Click compatible devices associated with your AWS account.

UnclaimDevice.documentation: Disassociates a device from your AWS account using its device ID.

UpdateDeviceState.documentation: Using a Boolean value (true or false), this operation enables or disables the device given a device ID.
